&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Head of Learning and Organisational Development&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an experienced Learning and Development professional to act as a senior member of the HR and Organisational Development team. This is an exciting role and an opportunity to work within a friendly, industrious team which works hard to enable SECAmb to deliver the very best patient services that it can.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working closely with the Director of HR &amp; OD, this role will require you to lead on the development and implementation of Learning and Development actions within the organisation and work on system and policy improvements within the Trust. You will be a key enabler in delivering against the Trust&#39;s aims and objectives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To be successful in this role, you will need demonstrable senior management experience within a diverse Learning &amp; OD team with specialist knowledge of NHS working practices.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are a current SECAmb employee, by applying for this position, if successful you will move to the terms and conditions associated with the post. Any unsocial hours payments will be paid under the Section 2 agreement of agenda for change. Section 2 unsocial hours will need to be claimed via your monthly timesheet. More information regarding Section 2 can be found in the Agenda for Change handbook and on the &lt;strong&gt;our dedicated Section 2 page on The Zon&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;e.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Informal enquiries are very warmly welcomed by Ali Mohammed, Executive Director of HR &amp; OD - ali.mohammed@secamb.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameAli MohammedEmail addressali.mohammed@secamb.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
